{
  "stem": "25423.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I didn't like the idea, so I went out every morning at 4 o'clock, and I worked in outside of the city, far in the suburbs.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was under the Soviets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had there sort of a cooperative producing vegetables, and I used to go there because there it was quiet and we were not beaten.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We volunteered there, and as I liked agriculture and things of that sort, I enjoyed working there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, they were locals.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the locals had free labor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We used to bring our own food, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was a reasonably decent way to spend the day and go home at night.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Immediately.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were several Judenrats, and that is a complicated question.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think, again, this was very carefully described and studied, so I'd rather not go into details of the Judenrat mechanism.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Originally, these were leaders of the community, and they tried to protect the community.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "About four weeks after the Germans arrived, the general in charge of the city-- infantry general, not an SS-- imposed an enormous ransom on the Jewish community, and silver and all the precious things, jewelry, had to be brought to the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Otherwise, reprisals were threatened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, this-- carpets, people brought it simply to buy peace, and this was transported, probably, to Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This Judenrat was still organized and sensible group of people, headed by [NON-ENGLISH], Yousef [NON-ENGLISH] When they came to him and said, you have now to give us a few hundred people for labor camps, he refused.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, money, yes, cooperation, yes, human beings, no.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, they took him to a prison and shot him with the rest of the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the end of the story, and then a new Judenrat showed up.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
